Others: Namibia and Liberia will face off in Group H of the 2026 Fifa World Cup qualifiers on June 5, 2024 at the Orlando Stadium in Johannesburg.
Namibia made history by reaching the knockout stage of the Africa Cup of Nations (Afcon) for the first time earlier this year.
Tunisia has gone through a spell of underwhelming performances, needing penalties to beat New Zealand in an international friendly in March.

Equatorial Guinea will be hoping to resume their World Cup qualifying campaign on a positive note, but they will have a difficult task against Tunisia, who have won five of their last seven meetings against them.
